    • getElement

      public static Elements getElement(String query)
      Returns an Elements element based on a sloppy case-insensitive search by symbol or by first three or four characters in an element's name. Examples: Elements.getElement(brom); will return Elements.BR. Elements.getElement(BR); will return Elements.BR. At least four character are recommended for a name search, but not always required. For example, Elements.getElement(Ber); will return the first matching element in the table, Beryllium, even though the desired element could be Berkelium. Elements.getElement(bro); will return Elements.BR, because Bromine can not be easily confused with another element from the first three characters.
      Parameters:
      query - the search query by symbol or start of the name.
      Returns:
      the Elements element.
